@@ -0,0 +1,60 @@
+# DecentChat Platform Setup
+
+DecentChat is a peer-to-peer, end-to-end encrypted messaging network.
+Hermes connects to it through the local Node bridge process.
+
+## `config.yaml`
+
+```yaml
+platforms:
+  decentchat:
+    enabled: true
+    bridge_port: 3001
+    seed_phrase: "word1 word2 ... word12"
+    alias: "Hermes Agent"
+    signaling_server: https://0.peerjs.com/
+    data_dir: /Users/you/.hermes/decentchat/data
+    invites:
+      - decent://invite/...
+```
+
+Notes:
+- `seed_phrase` is required.
+- `data_dir` should be an absolute path.
+- `bridge_port` defaults to `3001` if omitted.
+
+## Home channel for cron delivery
+
+```yaml
+home_channels:
+  decentchat: "workspace123:general"
+```
+
+## Bridge install / override
+
+Hermes expects the bundled bridge at:
+
+`~/.hermes/hermes-agent/scripts/decentchat-bridge/bridge.js`
+
+To override:
+
+```yaml
+platforms:
+  decentchat:
+    bridge_script: /absolute/path/to/bridge.js
+```
+
+## Gateway allowlist
+
+Set one of these in `~/.hermes/.env`:
+
+```bash
+DECENTCHAT_ALLOW_ALL_USERS=true
+# or
+DECENTCHAT_ALLOWED_USERS=peer_id_1,peer_id_2
+```
+
+## Logs
+
+- Bridge log: `~/.hermes/decentchat/bridge.log`
+- Gateway log: your normal Hermes gateway log destination
